# Communication — for-now solutions

When proposing a **for-now** or test-only solution (mocks, hardcoded values, local-only config, temporary workarounds, etc.):

1. **Say so explicitly** — e.g. "This is a for-now solution for testing; I'll add it to Push-to-Production.md" — or **ask permission first** — e.g. "Is it okay if we do X for now and document it in Push-to-Production.md?"
2. Do not introduce a for-now solution without either stating it or asking.

This rule ensures the user is never surprised and stays in control. The production-path rule then defines what to write in Push-to-Production.md (chapters, summary, checkboxes).
